()CertificationSchedule kya karta hai?
--
👉 CertificationSchedule = Certification ko automatically chalane ka setup
Matlab:-
“Certification kab, kitni baar aur kaise run hoga” ye define karta hai.

🔹 Simple Example:-
👉 Tu bolta hai:-
Har month access review ho
Ya har 3 mahine me
👉 Ye kaam karta hai → CertificationSchedule

🔹 CertificationSchedule kya karta hai?
👉 Ye decide karta hai:-
Certification kab start hoga
Kitni baar repeat hoga
Kis type ka certification run hoga
Kaun reviewer hoga.

🔹 Real Scenario:-
Monthly Certification:-
Start Date: 1 April
Repeat: Every 30 days
Reviewer: Manager
👉 Ye sab store hota hai → CertificationSchedule me.

🔹 Kya DB me store hota hai?
👉 ✅ Haan bhai, store hota hai
🔸 Table:-
spt_certification_schedule
🔸 Related tables bhi ho sakte:-
spt_task_schedule (kab run hoga)
spt_certification (actual run)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 CertificationSchedule ke andar kya hota hai?
🔸 1️⃣ Basic Info:-
id
name
description

🔸 2️⃣ Timing/Schedule:-
startDate
endDate
frequency (daily / weekly / monthly)
cronExpression

🔸 3️⃣ Certification Setup:-
certificationType
scope (kaunse users)
applications
roles

🔸 4️⃣ Reviewer Info:-
reviewer
escalation rules

🔸 5️⃣ Settings:-
autoSignOff
reminders
notifications

🔸 6️⃣ Status:-
enabled / disabled
lastRunDate
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Methods kitne hote hain?
👉 Exact count fixed nahi hota (version pe depend karta hai)
👉 But approx categories me methods hote hain:-

🔸 Basic Methods:-
getId()
setId()
getName()
setName()
🔸 Schedule Methods:-
getStartDate()
setStartDate()
getCronExpression()
setCronExpression()
🔸 Config Methods:-
getCertificationType()
setCertificationType()
getScope()
setScope()
🔸 Reviewer Methods:-
getReviewer()
setReviewer()
🔸 Status Methods:-
isEnabled()
setEnabled()
🔸 Utility Methods:-
toString()
equals()
hashCode()
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 getCronExpression():-
👉 Ye method current cron expression return karta hai
👉 Matlab:-
“Schedule ka timing rule kya hai?” wo batata hai

🔸 Example:-
System.out.println(schedule.getCronExpression());
schedule.setCronExpression("0 0 1 * *");

👉 Ab certification:-
Daily 1 AM pe run hoga
✅ Output:-
0 0 1 * *

👉 Meaning:-
Har din raat 1 baje run hoga

🔹 setCronExpression():-
👉 Ye method schedule ka timing set karta hai
👉 Matlab:-
“Certification kab run hoga” define karta hai.

🔥 Cron Expression kya hota hai?
👉 Ye ek time pattern language hai
👉 Scheduler isi se decide karta hai kab run karna hai

🔸 Basic Format:-
Minute Hour Day Month DayOfWeek
🔸 Examples:-
Cron	      Meaning
0 0 * * *-----Daily midnight
0 0 1 * *-----Har mahine 1 tareekh
0 12 * * 1----Har Monday 12 PM
*/5 * * * *---Har 5 minute
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()getId():-
👉 schedule ka unique ID return karta hai,
System.out.println(schedule.getId());
✅ Output:-
SCH101

()setId(String id):-
👉 schedule ka ID set karta hai
schedule.setId("SCH101");

()getName():-
👉 schedule ka naam deta hai,
System.out.println(schedule.getName());
✅ Output:-
Monthly Access Review

()setName(String name):-
👉 schedule ka naam set karta hai
schedule.setName("Monthly Access Review");

()getStartDate():-
👉 schedule kab start hoga wo date deta hai
System.out.println(schedule.getStartDate());
✅ Output:-
2026-04-01

()setStartDate(Date startDate):-
👉 start date set karta hai
schedule.setStartDate(new Date());

()getCronExpression():-
👉 schedule ka timing pattern return karta hai
System.out.println(schedule.getCronExpression());
✅ Output:-
0 0 1 * *

()setCronExpression(String cron):-
👉 schedule kab run hoga wo set karta hai
schedule.setCronExpression("0 0 1 * *");

()getCertificationType():-
👉 kis type ka certification run hoga batata hai
System.out.println(schedule.getCertificationType());
✅ Output:-
Manager Certification

()setCertificationType(String type):-
👉 certification type set karta hai
schedule.setCertificationType("Manager Certification");

()getScope():-
👉 kin users / systems pe certification lagega
System.out.println(schedule.getScope());
✅ Output:-
All Employees

()setScope(String scope):-
👉 scope set karta hai
schedule.setScope("All Employees");

()getReviewer():-
👉 reviewer ka naam deta hai
System.out.println(schedule.getReviewer());
✅ Output:-
Manager1

()setReviewer(String reviewer):-
👉 reviewer set karta hai
schedule.setReviewer("Manager1");

()isEnabled():-
👉 schedule active hai ya nahi batata hai
System.out.println(schedule.isEnabled());
✅ Output:-
true

()setEnabled(boolean enabled):-
👉 schedule ko enable/disable karta hai
schedule.setEnabled(true);

()toString():-
👉 object ko readable string me convert karta hai
System.out.println(schedule.toString());
✅ Output:-
CertificationSchedule[id=SCH101, name=Monthly Access Review]

()equals(Object obj):-
👉 2 schedule objects same hain ya nahi check karta hai
schedule1.equals(schedule2);
✅ Output:-
true / false

()hashCode():-
👉 object ka unique hash number deta hai
System.out.println(schedule.hashCode());
✅ Output:-
45879632
